venice.hub

Class VeniceWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • venice.hub.VeniceWriter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DiskWriter, IIOWriter, RSBWriter

    public abstract class VeniceWriter
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
    Abstract class for writing data from TTEQueue to a target.

    Gets data from TTEQueue and writes it to the target. The target is specified by the subclass. A subclass should be started as a Thread, like this:
    ANewWriter = new ANewWriter();
    ThreadForANewWriter = new Thread(ANewWriter, "VH_ANewWriter");
    ThreadForANewWriter.start();

    See Also:
    TTEQueue, DiskWriter, IIOWriter

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        protected void initialize()
        Prepare everything needed to write to target. Will be called by the constructor, so an implementing class should not override the constructor.

        For example: A disk writer has to open file. A net writer has to create slots, and so on.

      • isInitialized

        public boolean isInitialized()
        Checks, if the writer is ready to work.
        Returns:
        true if writer is ready to work, else false

      • isFinished

        public boolean isFinished()
        Returns true if this Thread can be safely killed.

        After the call of stopThread this Thread will try to get into a safe closing state. For example every open file will be closed.

        Returns:
        true if it is safe to kill this thread

      • pause
